<section style="padding:72px 24px 40px;"><div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;"><div class="rich"><p>Beatrice is the Gage County seat, about 40 minutes south of Lincoln, and its housing stock reflects a lot of decades of building. Many homes here were finished long before current egress rules existed, so basement bedrooms that have been used for years without a proper way out are more common than most owners realize. That gap tends to show up at the worst possible time, when a home inspector walks through during a sale and flags an illegal bedroom.</p><p>Lincoln Egress Windows works with Beatrice homeowners who are selling a house with an unpermitted basement bedroom, finishing a lower level for the first time, or just want a safer, more secure basement window. We handle the full job, from the <a href="/egress-window-cost/">estimate</a> through the cut-in, window well, and final inspection sign-off, so you're not left guessing what code actually requires.</p></div></div></section>
